.\" cpoe - Cryptographic Proof-of-Process Authorship Witnessing
.\" Generated from clap CLI definition. Re-generate with: cargo run -p cpoe_cli -- man > docs/man/cpoe.1
.TH CPOE 1 "May 2026" "cpoe" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cpoe \- cryptographic proof-of-process authorship witnessing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cpoe
.RI [ command ]
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ arguments ]
.PP
.B cpoe
.I file
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cpoe
captures behavioral evidence during document creation and packages it into
cryptographically signed packets that prove a human authored content over time.
It provides an offline-verifiable alternative to AI detection by proving
.I how
something was written, not just what was written.
.PP
If invoked with a bare file path and no subcommand,
.B cpoe
starts tracking that file.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Core Workflow
.TP
.BI "commit " file " [-m " message "] [--anchor]"
Create a cryptographic checkpoint of a document. Checkpoints are chained
hashes with VDF time proofs that form an unforgeable timeline.
Alias:
.BR checkpoint .
.TP
.BI "log " [file]
View checkpoint history for a document, or list all tracked files.
Aliases:
.BR history ", " ls .
.TP
.BI "export " file " [-t " tier "] [-f " format "] [-o " output ]
Export evidence packet with declaration for verification.
Alias:
.BR prove .
.TP
.BI "verify " file " [-k " key "] [--output-war " path ]
Verify an evidence packet (.json, .c2pa) or database (.db).
Alias:
.BR check .
.TP
.B status
Show current tracking status and configuration.
.SS Document Management
.TP
.BI "track " [action] " " [file]
Track activity on a file or project. Actions: start, stop, status.
If called with just a file path, starts tracking.
.TP
.BI "link " source " " export " [-m " message ]
Link an export/derivative (PDF, EPUB, DOCX) to a tracked source document.
Creates a cryptographic binding between the source evidence chain and
the derivative.
.TP
.BI "snapshot " action
Manage document snapshots. Actions: save, list, diff, restore.
.SS Identity and Security
.TP
.BI "identity " [options]
Show or recover your cryptographic identity.
Options:
.BR --fingerprint ", " --did ", " --mnemonic ", " --recover .
Alias:
.BR id .
.TP
.BI "fingerprint " action
Manage behavioral typing fingerprints. Actions: status, export, reset.
Alias:
.BR fp .
.TP
.BI "credential " action
Manage authorship credentials and verifiable presentations.
.SS Analysis and Reporting
.TP
.BI "forensics " action
Detailed forensic analysis of writing sessions.
Actions: analyze, compare, timeline.
.TP
.BI "report " file " [-f " format ]
Generate a Written Authorship Report (WAR). Formats: html, json.
.TP
.BI "beacon " action
Temporal beacon attestation. Actions: fetch, status, anchors.
.SS Configuration
.TP
.BI "config " action
Manage configuration. Actions: show, edit, reset, path.
Alias:
.BR cfg .
.TP
.B calibrate
Re-calibrate VDF performance for this machine (hidden).
.SS Utility
.TP
.BI "completions " shell
Generate shell completions (bash, zsh, fish, powershell, elvish).
.TP
.B man
Display the user manual.
.SH EVIDENCE TIERS
Per draft-condrey-rats-pop:
.TP
.B basic (T1)
VDF proof only (offline)
.TP
.B standard (T2)
+ keystrokes + timing (recommended)
.TP
.B enhanced (T3)
+ behavioral analysis + hardware attestation
.TP
.B maximum (T4)
+ all external anchors + full attestation
.SH EXPORT FORMATS
.TP
.B json
Machine-readable evidence packet
.TP
.B html
Self-contained HTML report
.TP
.B pdf
Signed PDF with anti-forgery security features
.TP
.B c2pa
C2PA Content Credentials manifest with embedded VC
.SH BASIC WORKFLOW
.IP 1. 4
.B cpoe essay.txt
\- Start tracking a file
.IP 2. 4
Write your document
.IP 3. 4
.B cpoe commit essay.txt -m "first draft"
\- Create checkpoint
.IP 4. 4
Continue writing
.IP 5. 4
.B cpoe commit essay.txt -m "revisions"
\- More checkpoints
.IP 6. 4
.B cpoe export essay.txt -t standard
\- Export evidence
.IP 7. 4
.B cpoe verify evidence.json
\- Verify evidence
.SH ENHANCED WORKFLOW
For strongest evidence with keystroke tracking and PDF reports:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ cpoe track start paper.tex
$ # ... write for several hours ...
$ cpoe commit paper.tex -m "Final version"
$ cpoe track stop
$ cpoe export paper.tex -t enhanced -f pdf -o paper-proof.pdf
$ cpoe link paper.tex paper.pdf -m "Published PDF"
.fi
.RE
