.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CPOE_DATA_DIR
Override default data directory (~/.writersproof)
.TP
.B CPOE_BEACONS_ENABLED
Enable/disable temporal beacons (true/false)
.TP
.B EDITOR
Editor for
.B cpoe config edit
.SH PRIVACY
The keystroke tracking feature counts keystrokes but does NOT capture which
keys are pressed. This is NOT a keylogger. Only event counts, inter-key
intervals, and timing jitter are recorded. Content is never stored.
.SH TEMPORAL BEACONS
Beacons (drand + NIST) are enabled by default via WritersProof. They anchor
checkpoints to independent, publicly verifiable time sources. Use
.B --no-beacons
on export to disable (caps security level at T2).
